Constructor = block of code similar to a method that is executed when we create an object(call).

Why do we need it? - constructor initializes the object

How to create a constructor?
1-constructor name must be same as a class
2-not return type

Type of the constructors
nor arguments
parametrized

this key word- is used to refer to current object

this can be used with variables and methods

this. used to refer to the instance variables.
In situation when local variable have same name as instance => we use this. to differentiate and refer to the instance variable

this can be used to refer to the instance methods as well